Definition 18. If it exists, the categorical model structure on the category $\mathsf{Cat}_{\mathsf{E}}$ is the model structure such that $\triangleright$ the weak equivalences are the functors $F$ from $(\mathscr{C},\mu,u)$ to $(\mathscr{C}^{\prime},\mu^{\prime},u^{\prime})$ such that $F_{x,y}:\mathscr{C}(x,y)\to\mathscr{C}^{\prime}(F(x),F(y))$ is a weak equivalence of $\mathsf{E}$ for any $x,y\in Ob(\mathscr{C})$, and such that $\pi_{0}(F):\pi_{0}(\mathscr{C})\to\pi_{0}(\mathscr{C}^{\prime})$ is an essentially surjective functor. $\triangleright$ the (large) set of cofibrations is the smallest subset of the set of functors which is stable under pushouts, transfinite compositions and retracts and which contains the functor $\emptyset\to*_{\mathbb{1}}$ and, for any cofibration $f:X\to Y$ of $\mathsf{E}$, the functor $[1]_{f}:[1]_{X}\to[1]_{Y}$.
Definition 27. A counital coassociative coalgebra $(V,w,\tau)$ is a comonoid in the category of chain complexes. We denote by $\mathsf{uCog}$ the category of such coalgebras.
Definition 1. Let $(\mathsf{E},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ and $(\mathsf{F},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ be two monoidal categories. A monoidal adjunction between them is an adjunction $\tikzcd[ampersandreplacement=\&]\mathsf{E}\arrow[r,shiftleft,"L"]\&\mathsf{F}% \ ,\arrow[l,shiftleft,"R"]$ together with a natural isomorphism $L(X)\otimes L(Y)\simeq L(X\otimes Y)$ which makes the left adjoint $L$ a strong monoidal functor. Subsequently, $R$ obtains the structure of a lax monoidal functor.
Definition 2. Let $(\mathsf{E},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ and $(\mathsf{F},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ be two monoidal categories, and let $F,G:\mathsf{C}\to\mathsf{D}$ be two lax monoidal functors between them. A natural transformation $\phi:F\to G$ is monoidal if the following diagrams commute $\tikzcd[ampersandreplacement=\&]{F(X)\otimes F(Y)}\arrow[r]\arrow[d,"\phi(X)% \otimes\phi(Y)"^{\prime}]\&{F(X\otimes Y)}\arrow[d,"\phi(X\otimes Y)"]\\ {G(X)\otimes G(Y)}\arrow[r]\&G(X\otimes Y)\ \ \ \ \tikzcd[ampersandreplacement% =\&]\&\mathbb{1}\arrow[ld]\arrow[rd]\\ F(\mathbb{1})\arrow[rr,"\phi(\mathbb{1})"^{\prime}]\&\&G(\mathbb{1})\ ,$ for any objects $X,Y$ of the category $\mathsf{C}$.
Definition 7. We denote by $*_{\mathbb{1}}$ the $\mathsf{E}$-enriched category with one object $0$ such that $*_{\mathbb{1}}(0,0)=\mathbb{1}_{\mathsf{E}}\ .$
Definition 24 (Joyal, Lurie). [Lur09] The Joyal model category $\mathsf{sSet}_{J}$ is the category of simplicial sets $\mathsf{sSet}$ equipped with the model structure whose cofibrations are monomorphisms and weak equivalences are maps $f$ such that $W_{c}(f)$ is a weak equivalence for the categorical model structure on $\mathsf{Cat}_{\square_{c}}$. The fibrant objects are the quasi-categories. Moreover, this is a cartesian closed monoidal model category.
Definition 14. Let $\mathsf{C}$ be a category tensored-cotensored-enriched over $\mathsf{E}$. We denote by $\mathsf{C}^{\{\mathsf{E}\}}$ the $\mathsf{E}$-category whose objects are the objects of $\mathsf{C}$ and such that for any $x,y\in\mathsf{C}$, $\mathsf{C}^{\{\mathsf{E}\}}(x,y)=\{x,y\}\ .$ The composition is given by the adjoint of the following composite map $x\triangleleft(\{x,y\}\otimes\{y,z\})\simeq(x\triangleleft\{x,y\})% \triangleleft\{y,z\}\to y\triangleleft\{y,z\}\to z\ ,$ and the unit $\mathbb{1}\to\{x,x\}$ by the adjoint of the map $x\triangleleft\mathbb{1}\simeq x\ .$
Definition 3. A bilinear monoidal category $(\mathsf{E},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ is a monoidal category such that $\mathsf{E}$ is cocomplete and such that the bifunctor $-\otimes-$ commutes with colimits separately on both sides.
Definition 12 ((Co)tensorisation). Let $(\mathsf{E},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ be a monoidal category and let $\mathsf{C}$ be a category. $\triangleright$ A tensorisation of $\mathsf{E}$ on $\mathsf{C}$ is a functor $-\triangleleft-:\mathsf{C}\times\mathsf{E}\rightarrow\mathsf{C}$ together with functorial isomorphisms $\begin{cases}X\triangleleft(\mathcal{A}\otimes\mathcal{B})\simeq(X% \triangleleft\mathcal{A})\triangleleft\mathcal{B}\ ,\\ X\triangleleft\mathbb{1}\simeq X\ ,\end{cases}$ for any $X\in\mathsf{C}$, any $\mathcal{A},\mathcal{B}\in\mathsf{E}$; these functors are compatible with the monoidal structure of $\mathsf{E}$ in the sense that the following diagrams are commutative $\xymatrix{\big{(}(X\triangleleft\mathcal{A})\triangleleft\mathcal{B}\big{)}% \triangleleft\mathcal{C}\ar[r]\ar[d]&\big{(}X\triangleleft(\mathcal{A}\otimes% \mathcal{B})\big{)}\triangleleft\mathcal{C}\ar[r]&X\triangleleft\big{(}(% \mathcal{A}\otimes\mathcal{B})\otimes\mathcal{C}\big{)}\ar[d]\\ (X\triangleleft\mathcal{A})\triangleleft(\mathcal{B}\otimes\mathcal{C})\ar[rr]% &&X\triangleleft\big{(}\mathcal{A}\otimes(\mathcal{B}\otimes\mathcal{C})\big{)% }\ ,}$ $\xymatrix{(X\triangleleft\mathbb{1})\triangleleft\mathcal{A}\ar[rd]\ar[rr]&&X% \triangleleft(\mathbb{1}\otimes\mathcal{A})\ar[ld]\\ &X\triangleleft\mathcal{A}\ .}$ $\triangleright$ A cotensorisation of $\mathsf{E}$ on $\mathsf{C}$ is a functor: $\langle-,-\rangle:\mathsf{E}^{op}\times\mathsf{C}\rightarrow\mathsf{C}$ together with functorial isomorphisms $\begin{cases}\langle\mathcal{A}\otimes\mathcal{B},X\rangle\simeq\langle% \mathcal{A}\langle\mathcal{B},X\rangle\rangle\ ,\\ \langle\mathbb{1},X\rangle\simeq X\ .\end{cases}$ such that the duals of the above diagrams are commutative.
Definition 29. A dg conilpotent coassociative coalgebra (or dg conilpotent coalgebra for short) $(\mathcal{C},w)$ is the data of a chain complex $\mathcal{C}$ together with a coproduct $w:\mathcal{C}\to\mathcal{C}\otimes\mathcal{C}$ which is coassociative that is $(w\otimes\mathrm{Id})\circ w=(\mathrm{Id}\otimes w)\circ w$ and conilpotent, that is, for any element $x\in\mathcal{C}_{m}$, there exists an integer $n$ such that $w^{(n)}(x):=(w\otimes\mathrm{Id}^{\otimes n-1})\circ\cdots\circ(w\otimes% \mathrm{Id})\circ w(x)=0\ .$
Definition 20. Let $(\mathsf{E},\otimes,\mathbb{1})$ be a monoidal category. A monoidal segment $(H,\delta^{0}_{H},\delta^{1}_{H},\sigma_{H},\gamma_{H})$ is a segment $\mathbb{1}\sqcup\mathbb{1}\xrightarrow{(\delta^{0}_{H},\delta^{1}_{H})}H% \xrightarrow{\sigma_{H}}\mathbb{1}\ ,$ together with a map $\gamma_{H}:H\otimes H\to H$ such that $\triangleright$ the product $\gamma_{H}$ is associative, that is $\gamma_{H}(Id_{H}\otimes\gamma_{H})=\gamma_{H}(\gamma_{H}\otimes Id_{H})$, $\triangleright$ the product has a unit given by $\delta^{0}_{H}:\mathbb{1}\to H$, $\triangleright$ the morphism $\sigma_{H}$ is a morphism of monoids, $\triangleright$ the morphism $\delta^{1}_{H}:\mathbb{1}\to H$ is absorbant, that is the following diagram commutes $\tikzcd[ampersandreplacement=\&]H\simeq\mathbb{1}\otimes H\arrow[r,"\delta^{1}% _{H}\otimes Id"]\arrow[d,"\sigma_{H}"^{\prime}]\&H\otimes H\arrow[d,"\gamma_{H% }"]\&H\simeq H\otimes\mathbb{1}\arrow[l,"Id\otimes\delta^{1}_{H}"^{\prime}]% \arrow[d,"\sigma_{H}"]\\ \mathbb{1}\arrow[r,"\delta^{1}_{H}"^{\prime}]\&H\&\mathbb{1}\arrow[l,"\delta^{% 1}_{H}"]\ .$ A morphism of monoidal segments from $(H,\delta^{0}_{H},\delta^{1}_{H},\sigma_{H},\gamma_{H})$ to $(H^{\prime},\delta^{0}_{H^{\prime}},\delta^{1}_{H^{\prime}},\sigma_{H^{\prime}% },\gamma_{H^{\prime}})$ is a morphism of segment $f:H\to H^{\prime}$ such that $f\gamma_{H}=\gamma_{H^{\prime}}(f\otimes f)$. In a monoidal model category, a monoidal segment which is also an interval is called a monoidal interval.
Definition 26. Let $\mathbb{I}$ be the groupoid with two objects $0$ and $1$ such that $\mathbb{I}(i,j)=*\ ,\ \forall i,j\in\{0,1\}\ .$
Definition 16. A $\mathsf{E}$-model category is a model category $\mathsf{M}$ tensored-cotensored-enriched over $\mathsf{E}$ such that the enrichment of $\mathsf{M}$ over $\mathsf{E}$ is homotopical.
